# 4. Prepare Data

Aggregate `Sales` and `Budget Sales` at the `Product`.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
product <- coffeechain %>%
  group_by(`Product`) %>%
  summarise(`target` = sum(`Budget Sales`),
            `current` = sum(`Sales`)) %>%
  ungroup()
glimpse(product)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
Rows: 13
Columns: 3
$ Product <chr> "Amaretto", "Caffe Latte", "Caffe Mocha", "Chamomile", "Colomb…
$ target  <dbl> 27200, 30540, 84600, 63840, 134380, 57360, 75720, 67040, 50900…
$ current <dbl> 26269, 35899, 84904, 75578, 128311, 73151, 78162, 62248, 66772…
```
:::
:::


Compute the minimum, maximum and end of the the month sales.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
sales_report <- coffeechain %>%
  filter(Date >= "2013-01-01") %>%
  mutate(Month = month(Date)) %>%
  group_by(Month, Product) %>%
  summarise(Sales = sum(Sales)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  select(Month, Product, Sales)
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mins <- group_by(sales_report, Product) %>% 
  slice(which.min(Sales))
maxs <- group_by(sales_report, Product) %>% 
  slice(which.max(Sales))
ends <- group_by(sales_report, Product) %>% 
  filter(Month == max(Month))
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
quarts <- sales_report %>%
  group_by(Product) %>%
  summarise(quart1 = quantile(Sales, 0.25),
            quart2 = quantile(Sales, 0.75)) %>%
  right_join(sales_report)
```
:::



gtExtras 


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
report <- coffeechain %>%
  mutate(Year = year(Date)) %>%
  filter(Year == "2013") %>%
  mutate (Month = month(Date, abbr = TRUE)) %>%
  group_by(Product, Month) %>%
  summarise(Sales = sum(Sales)) %>%
  ungroup()
glimpse(report)
```

